The paper deals with predicting the future locations of people in first-person videos, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection and tracking. The use of wearable cameras also suggests a potential application in robotics (RO). The proposed framework involves a convolution-deconvolution architecture, which is a common technique in machine learning (LG) for tasks such as image segmentation and generation. The paper also mentions the use of target poses for predicting future locations, which could involve artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as pose estimation and action recognition.
